extracted_rules.rule_name: Standard setbacks by zone (apply in most cases)

Qualifiers.scope: Citywide residential zones listed (R-1 and specified R-1 lot-size variants), plus special lot types as defined in the table.
applicability: Applies to most properties unless a special setback applies or a larger contextual front setback applies (see related rules).
Applies to front, rear, interior side, and street side yards as indicated per zone or lot type.
exclusions: Front setbacks on named streets with special setbacks where those special setbacks override the standard (unless contextual is larger; see separate rule).
Front setbacks where contextual setback > 30 ft (contextual may control; see separate rule).
Street-side setbacks may be superseded by special setbacks on designated streets (see separate rule).

Variables.name: zone
Variables.description: Base zoning district for the lot.

Variables.name: lot_type
Variables.description: Lot classification as referenced in the table.

Variables.name: is_corner_lot
Variables.description: True if the lot is a corner lot (affects street-side setbacks).

Variables.name: lot_width_ft
Variables.description: Width of lot; used to determine ‘< 50 ft’ condition for substandard corner lots.

Variables.name: front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Required front yard setback (may be controlled by standard, contextual, or special setback rules).

Variables.name: street_side_setback_ft
Variables.description: Required street side yard setback on corner lots.

Constants.name: zone_standard_setbacks
Constants.notes: ‘contextual_or_20’ defers to separate contextual rule and 30 ft threshold.

Conditions.description: Apply zone_standard_setbacks when lot_type = standard and no special setback applies and contextual (if applicable) does not result in a larger required front setback (see contextual rule).
For lot_type = flag_lot, set setbacks as: front = 10 ft; rear = 20 ft; interior side = same as the base zone; street side = not applicable.
For lot_type = substandard_lot (non-corner), use substandard_lot_setbacks: front per contextual rule or 20 ft; rear = 20 ft; interior side = same as base zone; street side = 16 ft.

For lot_type = substandard_corner_lot_lt_50ft (corner lot with lot_width_ft < 50 ft), use substandard_corner_lot_lt_50_setbacks: front per contextual rule or 20 ft; rear = 20 ft; interior side = same as base zone; street side = 10 ft.
Interior side ‘see zone’ means: use interior_side_ft from zone_standard_setbacks for the applicable base zone.

Exceptions.description: Special setbacks (for certain streets) override standard setbacks for front and street-side yards, unless a larger contextual front setback applies (see special setback rule).

Relationships.description: Standard setbacks are the base layer; may be superseded by special or contextual rules.
Code sections referenced: 18.12.040(a) Table 2; 18.12.040(a,c,e,& i); 18.04.040(a); 18.040.030(84, 87, 91, 128, & 146); ‘as shown in table’ on pages 24–25.
Relationships.notes: Exact definitions of ‘contextual setback’ and special setback distances may be defined in the cited sections or tables not included in this text.

extracted_rules.rule_name: Front contextual setback threshold and application

Qualifiers.scope: Front yard setbacks for zones and lot types where the table indicates ‘Contextual or 20’.
applicability: Applies to front setbacks for: R-1 and R-1(7000/8000/10000/20000) standard lots; substandard lots; substandard corner lots < 50 ft.
Does not apply to flag lots (front setback is fixed at 10 ft per table).
exclusions: Superseded by special setback only for comparison when contextual > 30 ft (see special setbacks precedence).

Variables.name: contextual_front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Contextual front setback as defined by code (method not provided in this page).

Variables.name: front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Resulting required front setback after applying threshold logic and any special setback comparison.

Conditions.description: If contextual_front_setback_ft > 30 ft, the contextual setback applies to the front yard, subject to comparison with any applicable special setback (use the greater of contextual and special if both apply).

If contextual_front_setback_ft ≤ 30 ft or contextual_front_setback_ft is not determinable, the required front setback is 20 ft by default, unless a special setback applies that overrides the standard.

Exceptions.description: If a special front setback applies and contextual_front_setback_ft ≤ 30 ft, the special front setback overrides the 20 ft standard (special values not provided in this page; see referenced tables/codes).

Relationships.description: This rule feeds the ‘front’ value in the Standard setbacks by zone rule when ‘contextual_or_20’ is indicated.
When both contextual (> 30 ft) and special front setbacks are applicable, the greater value controls.
See 18.040.030(84, 87, 91, 128, & 146) for definitions/method of determining contextual setback (not provided here).

Qualifiers.scope: Properties on specified streets where special setbacks apply.
applicability: Applies to front and street-side setbacks on streets identified as having special setbacks.
Named streets in this page: Alma St; Arastradero Rd; Ash St; California Ave.
exclusions: Special setbacks do not alter rear or interior side setbacks unless otherwise specified in external tables (not provided on this page).

Variables.name: on_special_street
Variables.description: True if the lot fronts or sides on a street designated with a special setback.

Variables.name: special_front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Special front setback per street-specific standard (value not provided in this text).

Variables.name: special_street_side_setback_ft
Variables.description: Special street-side setback per street-specific standard (value not provided in this text).

Variables.name: contextual_front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Contextual front setback for comparison when > 30 ft (see contextual rule).

Variables.name: front_setback_ft
Variables.description: Resulting required front setback after applying precedence.

Variables.name: street_side_setback_ft
Variables.description: Resulting required street-side setback after applying precedence.

Conditions.description: If on_special_street = true, special setbacks override standard setbacks for front and street-side yards.
If both a contextual front setback (> 30 ft) and a special front setback apply, the greater of the two values is required for the front yard.
For street-side yards: apply the special street-side setback when designated. No contextual threshold is specified for street-side in this page.

Exceptions.description: If contextual_front_setback_ft ≤ 30 ft, it does not displace the special front setback; the special front setback controls (if applicable).
Flag lots: street-side setback is not applicable; therefore special street-side setbacks do not apply to flag lots.

Relationships.description: Special setbacks supersede standard setbacks except when a larger contextual front setback applies (front yards only).
If both contextual and special apply to the front, use the greater (per note).
Exact special setback distances must be obtained from external tables/codes referenced on pages 24–25 and cited code sections.
